## Proposition 2.2.7

```coq
Lemma proposition_2_2_7 (X Y : subset 𝒰) : 
  X ⊆ Y ↔ X ∩ Y = X.
Proof.
We show both directions.
- We need to show that X ⊆ Y ⇨ X ∩ Y = X.
  Assume that X ⊆ Y.
  It holds that ∀ x ∈ X, x ∈ Y as (i).
  It suffices to show that X ∩ Y ⊆ X ∧ X ⊆ (X ∩ Y).
  We show both statements.
  + We need to show that (X ∩ Y) ⊆ X.
    It suffices to show that ∀ x ∈ X ∩ Y, x ∈ X.
    Take x ∈ X ∩ Y.
    It holds that x ∈ X ∧ x ∈ Y.
    We conclude that x ∈ X.
  + We need to show that X ⊆ (X ∩ Y).
    It suffices to show that ∀ x ∈ X, x ∈ X ∩ Y.
    Take x ∈ X.
    It suffices to show that x ∈ X ∧ x ∈ Y.
    We show both statements.
    We conclude that x ∈ X.
    We need to show that x ∈ Y.
    By (i) we conclude that x ∈ Y.
- We need to show that X ∩ Y = X ⇒ X ⊆ Y.
  Assume that X ∩ Y = X.
  It suffices to show that ∀ x ∈ X, x ∈ Y.
  Take x ∈ X.
  It holds that x ∈ X ∩ Y.
  It holds that x ∈ X ∧ x ∈ Y.
  We conclude that x ∈ Y.
Qed.
```

